        <td bgcolor="dimgray" colspan="2" ><img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="1">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;02/16/2001&nbsp;:&nbsp; 14:15:19</font>
        
		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&id=1368"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
        
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=1368')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&REPLY_ID=22843&TOPIC_ID=2984&FORUM_ID=7&CAT_ID=2&Forum_Title=Daily+Discussion&Topic_Title=Enforcing+of+Verant%27s+EBay+policies&M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>


        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">People buy virtual items to improve their chars.  Let's face it the economy is good in this country and a lot of folks have the money to spend on these things.  EQ is a very addictive game and it's all about items.  I sold on ebay and know who my customers are.  Most seem to be computer profesionals in their 20's and low 30's.  You get some kid out of college and after a year or so making 120k, single, no morgage, no children, no real expenses in life, they have the money to throw around on nice stuff to equip there char.  Buyers have jobs so most do not have the time to sit around and camp the Frenzied Ghoul for 14 hours to get a stupid sash.  It's easier to pay some clown like me to get it for them.  Those are the buyers.<BR>The sellers are people like me who do not camp one single thing to sell.  I do this for work.  There is no money in sitting in l guk for 14 hours camping the frenzied.  I make my money buy buying accounts, stripping the equip and then selling the account.  Most sellers do this.  Therefore the popular whine "Ebay farmers are ruining the game" is so off base it's comical.  All getting rid of ebay selling is doing is increasing the camping.  If these accounts which can no longer be sold are abandoned then the person who'd buy the FBSS now has to camp it, guess what?  Camping increases.  <BR>Now comes the kicker.  People like me have helped SoE and VI make this game what it is.  Yes I take some credit.  VI has made a very cool game but server overcrowding is a huge problem.  People like me allow the casual gamer to continue playing without getting bored.  They play longer.  We take accounts people no longer want to play and sell them to people who will play them.  We help the game and SoE's bottom line.  Now when a person is bored they cancel the account and everything just goes away.  SoE and VI are shooting themselves in the foot by doing this.  Most RP types will never be able to see this, most ebay haters will never see this.  <BR>So there you have it. I thank SoE and VI for not doing this sooner.  I've made some pretty good money.  It's been a real job for over a year now.  It's afforded me a nice living and now it's time to move on.  <BR>So for any of you ebay haters remember this.<BR>I have never camped an item in the game to sell.  Only a few people camp to sell on ebay, the real sellers are like me and don't camp.  No money in it.</P><P><BR> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

