        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">A few points here.</P><P>1. Letting someone buy a rare drop doesn't automatically mean that the spawn is camped less. If they weren't of a level to camp the item in the first place your not making any extra space for the rest of the server</P><P>2. Only a portion of items on ebay were from stripped accounts. The majority were coming from farmers. So the spawns that were supposed to be easier to camp cause mr rich guy isn't sitting there were instead being camped 24/7 by ebayers</P><P>3. Buying a level 50 character doesn't give you any skill at using it correctly. It hurts other players when someone who's never used a pet before lets one roam in a dungeon and it's the rest of the zone that gets trained. And, yes I know some people who bought accounts might have had high level characters from other classes, but they are just as likely to be people too lazy to get a character past 20.</P><P>4. Verant put a stop to it because they got sick of people petitioning or calling their toll free number complaining that they didn't get what they paid for. Some ebayers were "legit" but there were just as many defrauding people of money by falsely advertising what they were selling. Who got the blame for this, not the sellers. It was "Verant should do something about this" and guess what? they did. It only takes a small amount of time and money to build a good history on ebay, theres no real way of determining if someone is trustworthy</P><P>5. Many accounts bought on ebay were useless to the new owners. The other high levels on the server were aware the account was a sold one and wouldn't have anything to do with the new person. No guilds, no raids, no groups. How's that for a fun game? And guess again who had to field the complaints? Thats right, it was Verant</P><P>I don't like ebayers because no matter how you justify how you're making life easier for other players you're really just making it harder. </P><P><BR>Narben the Gnomish Gnecro<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
